description.excerpt: We explore and experiment the methods and processes of real-time 2D multiperson pose estimation described in the paper: https://arxiv.org/pdf/1611.08050.pdf

Resize each image to X, an array of images (s1,s2,3), where (s1,s2) is the image_shape parameter (default s1=s2=224).  
We require that s is divisible by 8. 
COCO annotations label the body joints(src/config.py KEYPOINTS) already, and we use these points to build confidence map of each image and store in Y. Y is an array of (s/8, s/8, NUM_KEYPOINTS). 
The confidence map is calculated using a Gaussian kernel and take max
Pass Z through the model using Adam optimizer. For each layer, evaluate trained Z and Y's mean square error to check convergence.
Preprocess X using VGG19 and store it in Z
